{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/go-bdd/gobdd/releases/20006325", "assets_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/go-bdd/gobdd/releases/20006325/assets", "upload_url": "https://uploads.github.com/repos/go-bdd/gobdd/releases/20006325/assets{?name,label}", "html_url": "https://github.com/go-bdd/gobdd/releases/tag/v0.4.0", "id": 20006325, "author": {"login": "bkielbasa", "id": 1235620, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEyMzU2MjA=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1235620?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/bkielbasa", "html_url": "https://github.com/bkielbasa", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bkielbasa/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bkielbasa/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bkielbasa/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bkielbasa/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bkielbasa/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bkielbasa/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bkielbasa/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bkielbasa/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bkielbasa/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "node_id": "MDc6UmVsZWFzZTIwMDA2MzI1", "tag_name": "v0.4.0", "target_commitish": "master", "name": "Adding predefined steps in testhttp package", "draft": false, "prerelease": false, "created_at": "2019-09-16T04:01:09Z", "published_at": "2019-09-16T07:42:13Z", "assets": [], "tarball_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/go-bdd/gobdd/tarball/v0.4.0", "zipball_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/go-bdd/gobdd/zipball/v0.4.0", "body": "Here's the full list:\r\n\r\n```golang\r\n_ = addStep.AddStep(`^I make a (GET|POST|PUT|DELETE|OPTIONS) request to \"([^\"]*)\"$`, testHTTP.makeRequest)\r\n_ = addStep.AddStep(`^the response code equals (\\d+)$`, testHTTP.statusCodeEquals)\r\n_ = addStep.AddStep(`^the response contains a valid JSON$`, testHTTP.validJSON)\r\n_ = addStep.AddStep(`^the response is \"(.*)\"$`, testHTTP.theResponseIs)\r\n_ = addStep.AddStep(`^the response header \"(.*)\" equals \"(.*)\"$`, testHTTP.responseHeaderEquals)\r\n_ = addStep.AddStep(`^I have a (GET|POST|PUT|DELETE|OPTIONS) request \"(.*)\"$`, testHTTP.iHaveARequest)\r\n_ = addStep.AddStep(`^I set request header \"(.*)\" to \"(.*)\"$`, testHTTP.iSetRequestSetTo)\r\n_ = addStep.AddStep(`^I set request body to \"([^\"]*)\"$`, testHTTP.iSetRequestBodyTo)\r\n_ = addStep.AddStep(`^the request has body \"(.*)\"$`, testHTTP.theRequestHasBody)\r\n_ = addStep.AddStep(`^I make the request$`, testHTTP.iMakeRequest)\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhat's more, I made `RequestKey` and `ResponseKey` so defining your custom steps should be easier.\r\n\r\n"}
